comments.author: siemenssx1
comments.text:
The performance mode is basically the device running on the marketed spec 
configuration...QHD screen, unthrottled CPU etc. WTF this shouldn't be an 
option, this should be NORMAL mode! 

I think it's really dishonest to limit the marketed specs on a mode that 
for most people, would find to be not suitable for daily 24/7 use. 
Performance indicate a short burst of high intense activity, IMO. Hence, it 
would be more logical if it overclocked the cpu for a short time, or boost 
the RAM speed or anything that EXCEEDS the factory specs.﻿
